author: hwright
msg: Ev2 shims: If we're not given a deleted base revision, assume it's the same as
This is required when eventually calling svn_editor_add_file/dir, as those
functions need to know if we are replacing something or just adding something
new.  To signal a replacement (which occurs when there has been a delete first),
we need this somewhat-bogus revision number.
This drops the number of test failures of ra_dav to 65 (with 1 XPASS).
(ev2_delete_entry): If the revision given isn't valid, use the parent base
